The paper deals with the realization of chirotopes (oriented matroids) of random point sets in a convex domain in $\mathbb{R}^d$. This is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and random sampling, which are topics in computer science theory (cs.DS) and probability theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper cites previous results on order types of random planar point sets, which suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT).
